com.ibm.team.repository.client.util

Interface IEvent

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IChangeHistoryEvent, ICommitEvent, IComponentHierarchyUpdateEvent, IConfigurationUpdateEvent, ICurrentChangeSetEvent, ILockEvent, IPropertyChangeEvent, IQueryEvent, ISharedItemChangeEvent, IWorkItemsModificationEvent, IWorkspaceEvent
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Event, PropertyChangeEvent, QueryChangeEvent, QueryExecutionStateChangeEvent

    public interface IEvent
    A description of an event originating from some event source.

    Subclass the base event class Event to declare a new class, or implement this interface directly if need be.

    Since:
    0.5
    See Also:
    IEventSource, IListener.handleEvents(List)

    • Method Detail

      • getEventSource

        IEventSource getEventSource()
        Returns the event source that originated this event.
        Returns:
        the event source that reported this event, which is never null

      • getEventType

        java.lang.String getEventType()
        Returns the type of event that has occurred. The valid types of events are defined by implementers of this class.

        Events types are unique strings that follow package naming convention.

        Returns:
        the type of event that has occurred, which is never null

      • getCategories

        java.util.List getCategories()
        Returns the non-empty list of categories for this event. Categories must be distinct non-null objects that can be compared with equals.

        An event listener is registered against a category, entitling it to receive notifications of events in that category. The list always includes the event's event type as returned by getEventType(), allowing client to register listeners for specific types of events.

        Returns:
        the non-empty list of non-null categories (element type: Object); the list is never null; the list is immutable
